# Frontend feature patterns

## Directory structure

Features live in `apps/web/src/features/<feature-name>/` or `apps/online-order/src/features/<feature-name>/`. Every feature follows one of two variants:

**Generated API** (OpenAPI endpoints exist): `components/`, `validators/`, page file, `index.ts`. Hooks and types come from `@/generated/api`.

## Golden paths

| Task | Do this |
|------|---------|
| New CRUD backoffice page | Copy `features/catalog/products/` → **`mira-frontend-feature`** skill |
| Data table page | **`mira-data-table`** skill |
| Backend route added/changed | `cd apps/web && bun run api:generate` or `cd apps/online-order && bun run api:generate` — then import from `@/generated/api` |
| Manual / non-OpenAPI integration | **`mira-frontend-api-integration`** skill |

## Page structure

```
<Page>
  <Page.Header />
  <Page.Content>
    <Page.Title title="..." description="..." actions={[...]} />
    <Card>
      <DataTable table={table} loading={isLoading}>
        <DataTableToolbar table={table} />
      </DataTable>
    </Card>
  </Page.Content>
  <FormDrawerOrDialog />
</Page>
```

Call `useBreadcrumb([...])` at the top of every page. Use `nuqs` (`useQueryState`) for URL-synced search/filter/sort state. Debounce search with `useDebouncedValue`.

## Code style

- Named exports only, no default exports
- Function declarations (`function Foo()` not `const Foo = () =>`)
- `type` keyword for type-only exports
- `toast.success` / `toast.error` via `sonner`
- TanStack Table via `useReactTable` + `createColumnHelper<T>()`
- `<DataTableColumnHeader>` for sortable column headers
- `DropdownMenu` for row actions
- `lucide-react` for icons
